# UI Kit — Slides

A brand-faithful slide system for telling the Ganesh OS story. Five 1280×720 slide types, static HTML so they are directly editable and render without the bundle.

## Slides
- `TitleSlide.html` — cover: kicker pill, gradient headline, lede, footer mark.
- `BigStatSlide.html` — one load-bearing number (99 → 0) with a supporting metric row.
- `FenceSlide.html` — the single-writer rule as an ownership table (the core concept).
- `CaseStudySlide.html` — problem → pattern → receipt in three domain-accented columns.
- `QuoteSlide.html` — one strong idea on the alt background, with a cyan-highlighted phrase.

## System
Each links `styles.css` for tokens. Shared motifs: blurred orbs + faded grid, white→grey gradient headline fill, mono uppercase eyebrows, 84px-ish margins, domain-colored accents. Copy follows house style (sentence case, no em dashes, numbers as proof).

## Use
Open any file to preview/edit. To assemble a deck, copy these into a `deck_stage.js` shell (one `<section>` per slide) in a consuming project, or export to PPTX. Source narrative: `docs/story.md`, `docs/case-studies.md`, `docs/design-patterns.md`.
